original: An agricultural tool with a long handle and long, thick, widely separated pointed tines (also called prongs) used to lift and pitch (throw) loose material, such as hay, straw or leaves. Also capable of stabbing through soft enough objects.
english: An agricultural tool with a long handle and long, thick, widely separated pointed tines (also called prongs) used to lift and pitch (throw) loose material, such as hay, straw or leaves. Also capable of stabbing through soft enough objects.
czech: Zemědělský nástroj s dlouhou rukojetí a dlouhými, hustými, široce oddělenými špičatými hroty, používanými ke zvedání a rozhazování sypkého materiálu, jako je seno, sláma nebo listy. Je také schopen bodnout dostatečně měkkými předměty.

original: A meat tenderizer is a hand-powered tool used to tenderize slabs of meat in preparation for cooking.

original: A hand-held agricultural tool with a curved blade typically used for harvesting grain crops or cutting succulent forage chiefly for feeding livestock (either freshly cut or dried as hay).
english: A hand-held agricultural tool with a curved blade typically used for harvesting grain crops or cutting succulent forage chiefly for feeding livestock (either freshly cut or dried as hay).
